<figureCitation id="13002A46FFDF971B5EE218CEFCBB6D8B" box="[736,825,1481,1508]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1470,1496]" captionTargetBox="[207,1371,275,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,265,1433]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 2. Overview of the placentation in Paracephaelis Baill. A–K. Abaxial views of placenta and ovules. A’. Adaxial view of placenta and ovules with zone of attachment of the placenta indicated. A–C. Typical placentation type of Paracephaelis, with many ovules arranged at the periphery of the placenta.D–E. Idem, with fewer ovules. F–H. Idem, but ovules restricted to the top of the placenta. I. Typical placentation type in P. cinerea (A.Rich. ex DC.) De Block, P. comorensis De Block sp. nov. and P. trichantha (Baker) De Block. J–K. Idem, with fewer ovules. Drawn by Mr A. Fernandez. From Perrier de la Bâthie 13452 (P. tiliacea Baill., A, A’); Pervillé 633 (P. tiliacea Baill., B); Capuron 23451-SF (P. longipedicellata De Block sp. nov., C); McPherson et al. 14875A (P. saxatilis (Scott Elliot) De Block, D); Gautier et al. 4188 (P. gautieri De Block sp. nov., E); De Block et al. 1280 (P. bardotiae De Block sp. nov., F); De Block et al. 1048 (P. russata De Block sp. nov., G–H); Capuron 23073-SF (P. cinerea (A.Rich. ex DC.) De Block, I); Barthelat et al. 732 (P. comorensis De Block sp. nov., J); and Labat &amp; Pascal 2887 (P. comorensis De Block sp. nov., K)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358820/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 2F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13002A46FFDF971B5F4718CEFCD66D8C" box="[837,852,1481,1507]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[190,233,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[208,1398,1021,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-259@25.[189,1398,1006,1923]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 6. Paracephaelis bardotiae De Block sp. nov. A. Fruiting branch. B. Stipule. C. Bracteole, ovary and calyx. D. Fruit. Drawn by Mr A. Fernandez. From Bardot-Vaucoulon &amp; Andrianantoinina 933." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358828/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">6</figureCitation>
