<subSubSection id="C3216548FFDD97195CBF1FE6FAC46ED7" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8436C3FFDD97195CBF1FE6FED46A94" blockId="26.[189,342,737,763]" box="[189,342,737,763]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<heading id="D0CC81AFFFDD97195CBF1FE6FED46A94" bold="true" box="[189,342,737,763]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94FEAD1FFDD97195CBF1FE6FED46A94" bold="true" box="[189,342,737,763]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8436C3FFDD97195CBF1E08FEBD6B24" blockId="26.[187,1399,783,843]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Only known from Ankarana National Park in 
<collectingRegion id="49FFF821FFDD97195EBC1E08FCCB6B46" box="[702,841,783,809]" country="Madagascar" name="Antsiranana" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Antsiranana</collectingRegion>
II District, Diana Region (
<collectingRegion id="49FFF821FFDD971958771E08FAED6B45" box="[1141,1391,783,810]" country="Madagascar" name="Antsiranana" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Antsiranana Province</collectingRegion>
) (
<figureCitation id="13002A46FFDD97195CC61E36FEB06B24" box="[196,306,817,843]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="88.[189,232,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[390,1182,270,1707]" captionTargetId="figure-11@88.[363,1224,265,1712]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="Fig. 23. Distribution maps of Malagasy species of Paracephaelis. A. P. aristata De Block sp. nov. (black dot), P. bardotiae De Block sp. nov. (blue dot), P. capitulifera De Block sp. nov. (green dot), P. gautieri De Block sp. nov. (red dot), and P. grandifructa De Block sp. nov. (yellow dot). B. P. cinerea (A.Rich. ex DC.) De Block (black dot). C. P. longipedicellata De Block sp. nov. (black dot), P. orientalis De Block sp. nov. (blue dot), P. pauciflora De Block sp. nov. (green dot), P. ranirisonii De Block sp. nov. (red dot), and P. seyrigii De Block sp. nov. (yellow dot). D. P. russata De Block sp. nov. (black dot), P. sambavensis De Block sp. nov. (blue dot), P. saxatilis (Scott Elliot) De Block (green dot), P. sericea (Arènes) De Block (red dot), and P. tiliacea Baill. (yellow dot)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358868/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8436C3FFDD97195CBF1E76FE5E6BE4" blockId="26.[189,476,881,907]" box="[189,476,881,907]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<heading id="D0CC81AFFFDD97195CBF1E76FE5E6BE4" bold="true" box="[189,476,881,907]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94FEAD1FFDD97195CBF1E76FE5E6BE4" bold="true" box="[189,476,881,907]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Habitat and phenology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8436C3FFDD97195CBF1E98FE7C6BB4" blockId="26.[189,1399,927,987]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Low-elevation dry, deciduous or semi-deciduous forest; on limestone covered by sand or clay. Flowers: January; Fruits: November.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8436C3FFDD97195CBF1906FDAF6C74" blockId="26.[189,557,1025,1051]" box="[189,557,1025,1051]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<heading id="D0CC81AFFFDD97195CBF1906FDAF6C74" bold="true" box="[189,557,1025,1051]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94FEAD1FFDD97195CBF1906FDAF6C74" bold="true" box="[189,557,1025,1051]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Provisional IUCN assessment</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8436C3FFDD97195CBF1929FB3E6E26" blockId="26.[187,1399,1070,1609]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Critically Endangered: CR B2ab(iii). Since 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D40FFDD97195EB71928FCC36C27" authority="Block, 2022" authorityName="De Block" authorityYear="2022" box="[693,833,1070,1096]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Paracephaelis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bardotiae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94FEAD1FFDD97195EB71928FCC36C27" box="[693,833,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">P. bardotiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27C57AAFFDD97195F451928FC226C26" box="[839,928,1071,1097]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known from only two collections, it is impossible to estimate the EOO. The AOO of the species is estimated to be 
<quantity id="4CC39B26FFDD971958121957FBCB6C05" box="[1040,1097,1104,1130]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="km" value="8.0">8 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C4E9B8BFFDD971958491957FBD16C31" attach="right" box="[1099,1107,1104,1118]" fontSize="6" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">2</superScript>
, which complies with the Critically Endangered category under criterion B2. The 
<specimenCount id="9D3DFD4AFFDD97195F341974FC5D6CE3" box="[822,991,1138,1165]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
were collected in Ankarana Special Reserve in 1999 and 2002. The species thus occurs in a single location, which complies with the Critically Endangered category under sub criterion ‘a’ of criterion B2. The Ankarana Special Reserve was instated in 1956 and, legally, protection is complete (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B32FFDD97195EB819DFFC5F6C9C" author="Nicoll M. E. &amp; Langrand O." box="[698,989,1240,1267]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref69502" refString="Nicoll M. E. &amp; Langrand O. 1989. Madagascar: Revue de la Conservation et des Aires protegees. World Wide Fund for Nature, Gland, Switzerland." type="book" year="1989">Nicoll &amp; Langrand 1989</bibRefCitation>
). In reality, however, infringements into the reserve are common (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B32FFDD97195E2719FDFCD16D7A" author="Nicoll M. E. &amp; Langrand O." box="[549,851,1274,1301]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref69502" refString="Nicoll M. E. &amp; Langrand O. 1989. Madagascar: Revue de la Conservation et des Aires protegees. World Wide Fund for Nature, Gland, Switzerland." type="book" year="1989">Nicoll &amp; Langrand 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B32FFDD97195F6219FDFB3C6D7A" author="Cardiff S. G. &amp; Befourouack J." box="[864,1214,1274,1301]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="571 - 584" refId="ref66289" refString="Cardiff S. G. &amp; Befourouack J. 2008. La Reserve speciale de l'Ankarana. In: Goodman S. M. (ed.) Paysages naturels et Biodiversite de Madagascar: 571 - 584. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, WWF, Paris." type="book chapter" year="2008">Cardiff &amp; Befourouack 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Forests in the Ankarana Special Reserve are destroyed by bushfires and are cleared for slash-and-burn agriculture. In the last 25 years, the reserve has experienced an enormous influx of migrant miners hunting for sapphires. The miners undercut the forest soil and set up semi-permanent camps inside the reserve. Furthermore, forests in the Ankarana Special Reserve are threatened by illegal logging for hardwood, firewood, and wood for the production of charcoal, by hunting, and by the selective collection of plant species for medicinal or subsistence use (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B32FFDD97195E2118C0FCCE6D8E" author="Nicoll M. E. &amp; Langrand O." box="[547,844,1479,1505]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref69502" refString="Nicoll M. E. &amp; Langrand O. 1989. Madagascar: Revue de la Conservation et des Aires protegees. World Wide Fund for Nature, Gland, Switzerland." type="book" year="1989">Nicoll &amp; Langrand 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B32FFDD97195F5818C0FB316D8E" author="Cardiff S. G. &amp; Befourouack J." box="[858,1203,1479,1505]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="571 - 584" refId="ref66289" refString="Cardiff S. G. &amp; Befourouack J. 2008. La Reserve speciale de l'Ankarana. In: Goodman S. M. (ed.) Paysages naturels et Biodiversite de Madagascar: 571 - 584. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, WWF, Paris." type="book chapter" year="2008">Cardiff &amp; Befourouack 2008</bibRefCitation>
; Fondation pour les Aires Protégées et la 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B32FFDD97195DE618EEFCF56E6C" author="Biodiversite de Madagascar" box="[484,887,1513,1539]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref67702" refString="Fondation pour les Aires Protegees et la Biodiversite de Madagascar 2020. The protected area of Ankarana. Available from https: // www. fapbm. org / en / protected-area-ankarana [accessed 1 Sep. 2020]." type="url" year="2020">
Biodiversité de 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7653FFDD97195EA318EEFCAD6E6C" box="[673,815,1513,1539]" name="Madagascar" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Because of these facts, a reduction in the extent and quality of the habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D40FFDD97195E551B0CFD676E4A" authority="Block, 2022" authorityName="De Block" authorityYear="2022" box="[599,741,1547,1573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Paracephaelis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bardotiae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94FEAD1FFDD97195E551B0CFD676E4A" box="[599,741,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">P. bardotiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27C57AAFFDD97195EEE1B0CFCC46E4A" box="[748,838,1547,1573]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is inferred. This threat, in combination with the low AOO and the single location, qualifies the species for Critically Endangered status.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8436C3FFDD97195CBF1B68FF7A6EE6" blockId="26.[189,248,1647,1673]" box="[189,248,1647,1673]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<heading id="D0CC81AFFFDD97195CBF1B68FF7A6EE6" bold="true" box="[189,248,1647,1673]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94FEAD1FFDD97195CBF1B68FF7A6EE6" bold="true" box="[189,248,1647,1673]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Note</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8436C3FFDD97195CBF1B99FAC46ED7" blockId="26.[189,1350,1694,1721]" box="[189,1350,1694,1721]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">This species is only known from two collections. Mature flowers and fruits are still to be collected.</paragraph>
